20025000.text: When the hell are you coming? We can't work together like this.

20025002.text:
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> I believed that if they gave them work, 
it was cheap, fast, and of good quality...

20025003.text: The items that should have arrived yesterday haven't arrived yet. Huh...

20025004.text:
This is the only way we can work together.
Ah... something that was unimaginable before.

20025006.text:
When I first came here, 
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Pungbaekmun</>, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Ereda</> people I was with him, but his eyes were different.

20025007.text: Everyone was desperate. By comparison, the <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> kids have no such sense of urgency.

20025008.text: Can you go and ask me some questions?

20025009.text: If I go and say something, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> will go crazy.

20025010.text:
Are you here to buy something? I'm a little busy...
Ask the newbie over there.

20025012.text: Oh my gosh! Did you tell me in advance? That? That's... that's probably...

20025013.text: (It's ok, I tell you to speak slowly)

20025014.text: Hold on. I'll check some paperwork.

20025015.text:
That's what... Ah! This hasn't been delivered yet?
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Geumgyeongcheolmun</> What the hell is the person in charge doing?

20025016.text:
Sorry. I will talk to the person in charge to check the item.
I will try to deliver it as soon as possible.

20025017.text: (Ask if it's okay to go and check it yourself)

20025018.text:
Why? No... you won't want anything.
Then I'll give you the location.

20025021.text: Ah. Are you talking about materials for facility management?

20025022.text:
You didn't get the message that it was delayed.
The delivery is probably cut off somewhere.

20025023.text: I'm sorry... the charcoal is not available right now.

20025025.text:
Originally, I used to make charcoal using wood on the north shore.
Now I can't go north because of <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>it's dark</>.

20025026.text: (then asks how to make a fire)

20025027.text: As soon as you hurry, <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Jungbug</>'s oiled grass and <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Spiders</> I am trying to airlift the essence of

20025028.text:
Hey, so many!
You must have worked hard to bring it here.

20025030.text: Okay. Thank you for your hard work.

20025031.text:
Now that you can make a fire,
it works twice as fast... no, three times as fast.

20025033.text:
We'll take care of that stuff first!
Don't worry.

20025034.text:
If you go and wait, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Illustration</> will
ship it for you.

20025035.text: Oh! Are you here? The goods have arrived. We can work on it now.

20025037.text:
I hope this isn't because I'm retiring from <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</>, isn't it?
I brought it to you on time...

20025038.text:
It's not like that... Still, I'm working at <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Foster</>
I'm an adult, so I need to understand.

20025039.text:
It was unimaginable back in the day.
That was a good time. Everyone worked without sleeping.

20025040.text: <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Pungbaekmun</>, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Ereda</> People were polite and did a good job... .

20025041.text:
Well, now that I've decided to work with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>,
it doesn't make sense to talk about it in the past...

20025042.text:
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> I need to get along well with people.
Times have changed, so I have to adapt. Haha!

20025043.text:
When I was a <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</>Crew... that was <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Sea Moon Continent</>
Is that the first time you came? I did.

20025044.text: (I have an urgent business, I will listen later)

20025045.text:
Yeah? Then, I'll buy you a drink later.
Let me tell you a lot of interesting stories. Haha!

20025046.text:
Oh, and <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Geumgyeongcheolmun</> thanked you 
and asked me to come back again.

20025047.text: Welcome. What made you come here?

20025048.text: (You have a troubled expression on your face. What's going on?)

20025049.text:
Did I look like that?
Uh huh. It shouldn't be...

20025050.text:
Right now, there are many things like this...
The workers are unable to work.

20025052.text:
It is difficult to obtain working materials or fuel...
There is some problem inside the organization.

20025053.text:
I'm struggling
how to inspire workers in a situation like this.

20025055.text:
Then... the artisans here are absolutely crazy if they <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Spider</> fried.
If you hold on to that, I think it will help.

20025063.text: (there were a lot of them in the forest)

20025064.text: I'm glad. The workers are having a really hard time these days.

20025065.text:
It would be nice if we could bring the goods ourselves
and apologize too.

20025066.text:
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Drawings</> told them to go through
themselves for delivery, etc.

20025067.text: (It's right next door, but they say it's okay to just say it)

20025068.text:
Because it has a relationship with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Illustration</>
It's difficult to break that and communicate directly.

20025070.text:
So are we... hmmm.
Well anyway, materials are a problem... tools are a problem...

20025071.text:
The work is complicated... and I'm exhausted.
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>I wish people could sort it out a bit.

20025075.text: I see. Maybe you pay for <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>?

20025076.text:
I think it will be a hit if <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> comes to <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Sea and Moon Continent</>...
 It is said that it is a business that remains unconditionally.

20025077.text: How much did you pay? I just scraped everything I didn't have...

20025078.text:
Did you pay too much? You did it. You did it!
There are many other people who have suffered.

20025079.text:
I need to meet the person in charge and check it out...
Because I'm busy, I didn't respond properly.

20025080.text: (Ask who the person in charge is)

20025081.text:
This is <textColor=[78:148:215:255]><textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Park Bi-bi</> from <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Dohwasangjeon</>.
Why don't you go and talk? Please ask me if you don't listen.

20025082.text:
Are you here to see things? I'm a little busy right now...
If it's not urgent, how about next time?

20025084.text:
Ah... that's it? That's all written in the manual in the first place
What do you do when you come back here?

20025086.text:
I am calm. What do you want me to calm down?
No, what did I force you to come?

20025087.text: I'm so busy... I'll hear all sorts of strange things.

20025089.text:
This is <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Dohwajeon</>. That's also <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Yedo Port of the Sea and Moon continent</>.
 Orders come in from all over the place, and I'm too busy to process them.

20025090.text: (Ask if you can talk to me if you can help me with something)

20025091.text:
Okay! Can you get me <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>deer skin</>? 
Is it just picked?

20025093.text: Oh! Thank you. This will put out some urgent fires.

20025094.text: (then ask if we have time to talk)

20025095.text:
Yes. Excuse me earlier. 
I'm very busy these days.

20025097.text:
Ah. That's right. I'll meet and talk with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Lee Sa-min</>.
There must have been a misunderstanding.

20025098.text:
The cost of the move also includes the cost of shipping.
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</><textColor=[78:148:215:255]>I'm paying a lot of money for fostering</>.

20025099.text:
So you probably think the price is high.
I should explain the actual cost, etc.

20025100.text: (Then <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>I will pass it on to Lee Sa-min</>)

20025101.text: Yes, of course. I will listen carefully this time.

20025103.text:
Okay? I'll have to go and get an explanation.
It may be difficult to solve.

20025104.text:
It's not like I'm going to get anything in particular.
I came here with a bit of frustration...

20025105.text: They didn't listen to the story... They asked me to read the manual, so I felt a bit sad.

20025106.text: (If you meet <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> later, you will be informed of this situation)

20025107.text:
It would be nice if you did that. But... In the end, I have to do my best.
Actually, I was frustrated and wanted someone to listen to me.

20025108.text:
The environment here is poor and prices are high...
On the other hand, there are many jobs and the wages are high.

20025109.text:
So if you work hard, you'll be fine.
You have to work hard to support your family in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Vandal Lake</>!

20025110.text:
I met a <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>promising young man</> here.
I'm thinking of starting a business together.

20025112.text:
Really? If that's okay with you, would you like to meet <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>that young man</>
and listen to him? I think it might be helpful...

20025113.text:
(Why are you staring at me?
Is there something on your face?)

20025114.text: Can you... see? My passion and potential?

20025117.text:
I believe so.
I'm going to develop it.

20025119.text:
No... don't go.
Listen to me more.

20025120.text:
There's a solid plant over there in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Green Horn Forest</>.
I want to make a basket out of it.

20025122.text:
No... that's right. I can't get <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>Stem</> because of the monsters around.
Can I get some of them?

20025123.text: Is this? Let's check it out in a moment.

20025124.text:
Um... Oh! Great. This strength and flexibility!
What if I made a basket out of this?

20025125.text: It will be a specialty of <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Sea Moon Continent</>.

20025126.text: (Ask if the basket has any merit)

20025127.text: I'll look for that in the future.

20025128.text: (Talk about the last time we met)

20025129.text: Ah! Nice to meet you. You're the one who helped me, right?

20025130.text: At that time... it was really frustrating...

20025131.text:
Ah! I heard from <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Sea Moon</>.
Basket material <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>Stem</> You saved me.

20025132.text:
Baskets made like that have
very good reviews! There's been a riot.

20025134.text:
But there is a problem. The <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>stem</> is also the property of the country...
It should not be developed without permission.

20025136.text:
In <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</>. They said you shouldn't trade without permission.
Can you take a look at this?

20025137.text:
Strictly speaking, it's not wrong.
I usually don't put any restrictions on that, but...

20025139.text:
Then I'll see if there's a way.
 Talk to someone <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Foster</> and I'll find a way.

20025140.text: But what's so great about that basket?

20025142.text: Then go to the craftsman and ask him to make a sample for you.

20025143.text: Let me go to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</> and negotiate.

20025144.text: Sample? <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Ho-Ryong Kwak</> or can he help you?

20025145.text: (Still said to be the most reliable person)

20025146.text:
Okay. Please wait a moment.
Because this isn't something that comes out of nowhere.

20025148.text:
I need mental preparation.
Is it a little artistic soul?

20025150.text:
Um... are you going to pick it up right now?
Um... wait a minute... I'll make it right away!

20025151.text:
It's finished.
Oh! It looks good to me! It's a masterpiece!

20025152.text:
Is this? Well... it's good. I'll sell it.
It's light and feels good. The basic color is good even if you don't paint it...

20025153.text:
How is the cost going to come out? Will there be enough quantity?
How much should I sell? Profitability...

20025154.text: (Remembering <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Isamin</>'s story that suddenly came to mind)

20025155.text:
Yeah? I did... <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>The person in charge</> is sincere... 
He's inflexible.

20025156.text:
I don't know the difference between a big business and a small business.
Maybe it's because the value of trust is set too low.

20025157.text: I'm not going to see a loss on the books. I'll be looking for profits.

20025158.text:
I hope you understand the bigger intentions...
I'll explain it again.

20025159.text:
Revisit the relocation price,
I'll come and find a way to help you adapt.

20025161.text: Don't worry, I'll take care of the basket anyway.

20025162.text:
You are here! Thank you.
I just received your message.

20025163.text: (Ask if something has already been dealt with)

20025164.text:
Yes, if you donate a percentage of sales from <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Foster</> to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Foster</> As a condition, 
I have been granted permission to use it commercially.

20025166.text: <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Kwak Ho-ryong</> seems to have been a good help.

20025167.text: (<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>tells the story of meeting Ho-ryong Kwak</>)

20025168.text:
Okay. I got help this time and I'm fine now.
I hope it will be helpful to those who come later.

20025172.text:
Ah! Small. 
Please listen to my story.

20025173.text:
I often work with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</> to do something in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Sea Moon Continent</>... .
There, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Crews</>is weird, so we can't work together.

20025174.text:
If you just open your mouth, you're proud of it. Don't do anything. This is not okay.
Nagging about nagging while working together...

20025175.text: Uh huh. They just came here to say that they did all the hard work...

20025177.text: I can't take it! This is why I can't work with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</> anymore!

20025178.text: (I actually did, but... how do you say it)

20025179.text: (If I say what I've heard, I think it'll just encourage a fight...)

20025180.text: (Would you like to go nearby and listen to the stories of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Crew</>?)

20025182.text: No... I feel like I'm talking behind the scenes when I say things like this, so it's a bit weird...

20025184.text:
Listen. So, I'm working with <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> people...
I'm not used to it, so I gave you some precautions.

20025185.text:
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>The person in charge</>, are you good at that kind of thing.
Pointing out people and kindly letting them know.

20025186.text:
Yeah. That's right. It's safe now, but
Is there one or two that died while pioneering there?

20025187.text: Die from illness, die from exhaustion, die from food spoilage.

20025188.text: Did someone die from spoiled food?

20025189.text:
It influenced me a lot. Eating is very important. 
It is directly related to combat power.

20025190.text: That's right. It's not an exaggeration to say that food is combat power.

20025191.text: But you put on an unpleasant face like hearing some kind of nagging...

20025192.text:
Ahh. I was just trying to tell you something nice...
You must be offended.

20025193.text:
So the sound got a little louder as I got a little more emotional.
That was my fault.

20025194.text:
Still, I wanted to help <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>these people</>...
Ahh... I'll pay more attention next time. I'll have to be more careful.

20025196.text:
Yeah? I've seen colleagues die in the past...
I guess you thought we were taking it too lightly.

20025197.text:
It's not without its exaggeration... but it's not that I don't understand
the situation.

20025198.text: (He didn't seem like a bad person)

20025199.text:
I'm not a bad person. He said he had such a thought.
I think I misunderstood.

20025200.text: The next time we meet, I'll try to solve it a little better.

20025202.text: Oh, and <textColor=[78:148:215:255]> <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Ho-Ryong Kwak</> of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Dohwasangjeon</> was looking for it. Joe.

20025205.text:
Recently, due to clashes between crews under <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</> and <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> I heard about it.
You said you intervened?

20025206.text: (He said he didn't mediate, he just told the story)

20025207.text: Yeah, I've heard the story too... I went to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Foster</> to communicate.

20025208.text: But you could be hurt if you do it wrong.

20025209.text: Wouldn't it be nice if you were in a position to receive orders from above to get along?

20025211.text:
So I'd like to hold a simple banquet to soften people's hearts
and talk about it after that.

20025212.text: I wish you could help with the preparations.

20025213.text: (tells the situation and asks to attend)

20025214.text: You must have used your hand again in <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Drawings</>.

20025215.text: I agree. It needs to be smoothed out like this.

20025216.text: I don't think I need to participate myself,

20025217.text: Is it ok to send <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Hayeon</> instead of me?

20025219.text: (Talk about the situation and ask to attend)

20025220.text: Huh? Are you telling me to play the role of a folding screen now?

20025221.text: Actually, it seems like an event that has nothing to do with us...

20025222.text: Isn't this, just come in moderation and give me a class?

20025223.text: (I don't know how to answer, so I'm listening quietly)

20025224.text: Okay... I'm not that ignorant either.

20025225.text: On our side, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Steel Fist</> will go on my behalf, okay?

20025226.text: (tells the situation and asks to attend)

20025227.text:
Okay.
We need a process to report and confirm to the upper level...

20025229.text:
The location and time have been confirmed,
If there are any problems, we will inform you separately.

20025230.text: You put a lot of effort into preparing.

20025231.text:
After feeding people and making them feel good...
I'll have to tell you a sensitive story.

20025232.text:
They are all good people.
It will work out eventually.

20025234.text: And... I have one more request.

20025235.text: <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>, including me, cannot afford to tour the current site.

20025236.text:
There are some parts that are unsettling because 
I don't understand properly what's going on in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Taerokrim</>.

20025237.text:
Of course I know 
through the <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Drawings</> and <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> organizations. We have to increase the part.

20025238.text:
What you will discover while exploring <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Taerokrim</> or <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Fertile Land</> 
I'd like you to tell me.

20025239.text: Can I ask you a favor?

20025240.text: The water here is clean and tastes good, so I've been drinking it for a long time!

20025242.text: Recently, many people have an upset stomach after drinking water.

20025243.text: Water is the source of all things, so we need to figure out the cause quickly.

20025245.text: Ummm... I'll have to look for something that can affect <textColor=[255:204:102:255]></> of valley water.

20025247.text: (Once you find as much as you can, will you investigate?)

20025249.text: (<textColor=[255:204:102:255]>Unhygienic and dangerous stuff</>, let's bring it with us)

20025250.text: Um... these are flowers that only grow in clean places!

20025252.text:
The <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>animal carcass</> should also be investigated closely...
There is a chance that the water died.

20025253.text:
Even if it's not, it's hard to understand that just because one or two animals died
the whole valley is polluted.

20025255.text: But I'm not sure what this <textColor=[255:204:102:255]>black substance</> is.

20025258.text:
Our <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Barong</> have a more developed sense of smell than humans...
That's not the case, it's just a story that raises suspicions!

20025259.text:
Someone may have intentionally sprayed it!
Hmm... I don't know... I'll just have to ask Perong Perong!

20025261.text:
Of course! <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Barongs</> don't care about trivial or important things
Talking and sharing anything!

20025265.text:
A friend of mine left to investigate <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Black Mud</>...
It hasn't come back in a few days.

20025266.text:
<textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Black Muddy</> The anti-development movement 
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Tea Doyeon</> I was a friend...

20025267.text:
It probably won't happen, but... 
After the person disappeared, I started to think of all sorts of things.

20025268.text:
So if you ever go there, 
I want to ask you to find a friend.

20025271.text:
Ah. I've never seen such a person before.
If there was, I would have rescued him.

20025272.text:
There's a lot of ground breaking here these days, so
it's dangerous to travel alone.

20025273.text: The <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>crocodiles</> also hide and pop out.

20025274.text:
How many days have passed?
It's a bit harsh to say this, but... it's vague.

20025275.text: (He said he would look for more)

20025276.text:
Wow. People are coming here.
I thought he was dead now...

20025278.text:
That's right. I'm <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Tea Doyeon</>.
Please help.

20025279.text: (He came to find him at the request of a friend)

20025282.text:
Ah~ <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Current</>! That's right. There was <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Current</>.
 <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Now</> Thanks to you. I have to admit this.

20025283.text:
Wow! The ground suddenly went out and I fell with a thump...
I don't know where this is...

20025284.text:
This! My leg hurts or hurts to death...
There are a lot of <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>crocodiles</> around, so I can't even go out...

20025285.text: I knew I was really dead. Please get rid of some <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>crocodiles</> around.

20025286.text:
Wow, thanks to you.
I admit this.

20025288.text:
The value of black mud here is at its peak these days.
It's just spreading here and there...

20025289.text:
There is also the phenomenon of ground breaking.
What is this... I am a complete witness.

20025290.text:
The animals that used to live here are just leaving.
I don't know why the <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>crocodiles</> don't leave... they just die.

20025291.text:
No. <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>crocodiles</> have to live too.
Because everyone has to live with their own territory

20025293.text:
Does <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> know about this? Don't you know?
I don't care if you dig or dig here.

20025294.text:
(If you meet <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>
I will tell you about this)

20025295.text:
I would be very grateful if you did that.
I'll go back to the village. Thank you!

20025296.text: Did you come to <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Paradise Valley</> for a waterfall tour?

20025298.text:
That's right. Excuse me.
Those who came for tourism may be in danger.

20025299.text:
I warn you in advance,
I recommend returning it if possible.

20025301.text: No... that's just my personal opinion, not a warning from <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</>.

20025303.text:
I use the <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Sunrise Slope</> a lot to go to the waterfall...
It's not a very safe place.

20025304.text:
But <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</> doesn't even officially warn you,
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> They have nothing to say.

20025305.text:
People say it's a superb view, so they come to see it.
It's good that there are no accidents and everyone is fine...

20025307.text: If it's okay with you, would you like to go down the <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Slope</> with me?

20025308.text: It doesn't matter as long as everyone has a small skill level, but...

20025309.text: People who don't are getting in and out.

20025310.text:
Actually, it's not just here.
There is a threat from <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Myomyeon</> here...

20025311.text:
There are also <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Paradise</>> down there.
You never know when they will attack people.

20025313.text:
It seems to be fine so far.
But people accidentally approached it and took damage.

20025314.text:
What is the purpose of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</> and <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</> when it's so dangerous
 Are we allowing tourism and leaving people unattended?

20025315.text:
The site is too dangerous.
If it were me, I would restrict access to the public.

20025316.text: Aren't those making these decisions not sure what <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Paradise Valley</> is all about?

20025317.text:
(If you meet someone high in <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</> or <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>, say
 will deliver)

20025318.text: Human over there! Come here for a second!

20025320.text:
What else are you checking while making eye contact!
This is the domain of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</>, so why did you enter?

20025321.text: (Explain that this is a passing path and has no other intentions)

20025322.text:
These days, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</> have been attacked by humans!
We are a peaceful race!

20025323.text:
I wonder if that's what you said,
and you came here to attack us?

20025325.text:
We <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</> aren't fools!
Show us our fists to those who invade the realm!

20025328.text:
Then please help us.
I will admit your innocence!

20025329.text:
Keep away the <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Spiders</> invading our realm!
And <textColor=[215:94:94:255]> Get rid of the spiders</>'s area mark!

20025330.text:
In the past, when humans came to this land,
they talked to the captain to determine their territory!

20025331.text: But why don't humans keep their promises!

20025332.text: Why do you keep expanding the realm of humans!

20025333.text: (I can't find a specific answer, so I decide to stay still)

20025335.text: (<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</> asks if they keep their promise)

20025336.text:
It's hard for me to speak on behalf of all <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</>.
It is up to the individual to keep their promises or not!

20025337.text:
But with the same promise as before, <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Daeseong Nakwon</> has both eyes open
What kind of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</>Would you mind breaking this promise?

20025338.text: There is no <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise </> who breaks their promise to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Paradise</> Goofy!

20025340.text:
You look like a good human!
But you can't trust all humans.

20025343.text: Ah. Sohyeok! Nice to see you here.

20025344.text:
I thought I should visit you anyway...
Have you been doing well?

20025345.text: (He said he still wanted to say something)

20025346.text: For me? Maybe... About what it is...

20025347.text:
((<textColor=[110:216:175:255]>He wants to tell the story 
people have told me about the situation in Paradise Valley</>)

20025348.text:
If it's okay with you, I'll change your seat... 
Because they say rats hear and do things at night.

20025349.text: (I don't think it's going to be such a secret story)

20025350.text:
It's better to be careful though. 
The daytime is said to be heard by birds.

20025351.text: Then tell me. Just in case you don't know, I lowered the volume a bit...

20025353.text: No... did that happen in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Paradise Valley</>?

20025354.text: (It would be nice if you could forward this story to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho</>)

20025355.text: Of course. Of course you should.

20025356.text:
I'm embarrassed. I've only read the report. 
You didn't really understand anything.

20025357.text:
I didn't know anything about the local conditions in <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>Paradise Valley</>.
Yet <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Saho< It's probably because</> couldn't find a place in the sea and moon continent.

20025358.text:
The system is not well organized, and the report is probably leaking somewhere.
Because a manager like me didn't do his job properly.

20025359.text: (I wonder if I can do better in the future)

20025360.text:
<textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Ho-Ryong Kwak</>... because he was friends with my father,
He raised me like his own son and trusted me...

20025361.text:
I am not able to do anything because I am such a poor person.
I am sorry.

20025362.text: (He said he was just trying to tell a story rather than blaming something)

20025363.text:
Thank you. I have nothing to say.
I'll do my best in the future.

20025364.text: (The seat is awkward, so he ends the conversation)

20025365.text: You've been doing great these days.

20025367.text: Can we ask you a favor too?

20025369.text: The expedition is trying to investigate the <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>wreck</> page.

20025370.text:
Originally, it would have to be done with the cooperation of the <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</> members
but...

20025371.text:
It seems that our expeditioners are a bit grumpy with 
the members of <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</>.

20025372.text: Of course we should fix that part...

20025374.text: Would you like to meet our crew and listen to our story?

20025379.text:
This page is <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>The Wreck's Tomb</>.
There seems to be something new.

20025381.text:
Are you here? 
Ah! I just found something really cool.

20025385.text: If you tell us this, it will improve our rating, right?

20025386.text: They say they're good people if you know what they're saying...

20025387.text: It felt like the <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Weeping</>Crew were looking down.

20025389.text:
Maybe I'm overthinking it...
Anyway, this is great information.

20025390.text: Slay <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Spears</>, and let's get their supplies.

20025391.text: Now, let's go explore the <textColor=[110:216:175:255]>wreck</> in earnest.

20025393.text: Okay. I know the location, so I'll leave first.

20025400.text: How great would it be if things worked out like this every time?

20025401.text: If you're not busy, I'd like to go with you every day!

20025403.text: I know. I just did it. Haha!

20025404.text: I'll be back soon... well... that's it.

20025405.text: (If you have something to say, please take it easy)

20025406.text: I'm a little reluctant to pass on <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Discipline</> in relation to <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Changdodan</> .

20025407.text: Can you tell me if it's okay with you?

20025408.text:
That... not to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Kogondae</>, but to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Sunnubi</> Daewon If you do,
the story will proceed smoothly.

20025411.text:
It's a place rarely visited by people...
In other words, <textColor=[215:94:94:255]>Spearhead</> is a good place to hide.

20025412.text: Thank you for providing such important information.

20025415.text: Including that, I will pass it on to <textColor=[78:148:215:255]>Kogondae</>.

20025417.text: (If that's the case, he said he would help)

20025418.text:
(He said it would be good if you go and hand them something
and talk)

20025419.text: (Ask how to know the new year)

20025420.text:
Didn't I tell you that I met a promising young man?
It is that young man!

20025421.text: (He said he didn't know it was Shin Hae-wol)

20025422.text: (Ask if the stem you saved was okay)

20025423.text:
Oh that's right! The stem! It's so strong and flexible!
It's perfect for making baskets!

20025424.text: Really? I think it will be a great help.
